So in Psalm chapter two, verse two and following, it says, the kings of the earth take their stand, the rulers take counsel together against the Lord and against His anointed, saying, let us tear their fetters apart and cast away their cords from us.

20:00.948 --> 20:05.793
But verse four says that he who sits in heaven laughs and he scoffs at them.

20:06.293 --> 20:11.218
See the Lord being king of kings and Lord of lords takes the heart of kings, earthly kings,

20:11.426 --> 20:15.611
and holds them in his hand and channels them like waters wherever he wishes.

20:16.372 --> 20:26.704
He can steer the heart of a good king to be better and raise the heart of a bad king like Cyrus, the king of Persia, to let God's people return, meaning God is the one who is ultimately in authority.

20:27.065 --> 20:31.530
So here the people are rejecting an ultimate authority for a lesser authority.

20:32.311 --> 20:36.036
And so in chapter nine, verses one and following, they got what they asked for.

20:37.017 --> 20:41.362
There was a man of Benjamin whose name was Kish, the son of Abil,

20:41.602 --> 21:02.645
The son of Zeror, the son of Bekarath, the son of Afaya, the son of Abingomite, a mighty man of valor, and he had a son whose name was Saul, a choice enhancing man, and there was no more handsome person than he among all the sons of Israel from his shoulders and up, he was taller than all of the people.

21:03.466 --> 21:05.728
You want a big strong tough guy king?

21:06.929 --> 21:08.311
Okay, there he is.

21:08.331 --> 21:11.314
Now here's the problem with externals, without internals.

21:11.394 --> 21:12.515
There's no longevity.

21:13.457 --> 21:18.503
When your responsibility outweighs your character, it's only a matter of time until you implode.

21:19.304 --> 21:20.666
And that's exactly what Saul is.

21:21.267 --> 21:24.110
Now he'll have blips on the radar and we'll talk more about him next week.

21:24.531 --> 21:32.701
He'll have blips on the radar where he does well, but by and large, he does not have the character, the godliness to carry the weight of responsibility.

21:33.002 --> 21:36.466
And so he ends up causing all kinds of damage.

21:36.962 --> 21:41.307
I wanna take the time that we have remaining and see if we can't maybe bring this together just a little bit.

21:42.108 --> 21:45.673
Because in many ways, I would make the argument, I'm not convinced much has changed.

21:46.413 --> 21:54.583
That I think as we read stories like this, there is a bit of a mirror that's held up for us and I just wonder if any of these things might apply to you.

21:55.565 --> 21:59.549
One, I think we have a similar tendency to reject the authority of God in our lives.

22:00.290 --> 22:02.032
Now for some, that's explicit.

22:02.914 --> 22:06.578
You hear the claims of the gospel and you reject them as fairy tale.

22:07.106 --> 22:11.150
You hear about God being the authority and you raise your fist at that.

22:11.171 --> 22:15.255
You are opposed to God, opposed to His Word, opposed to the work of the gospel.

22:15.675 --> 22:17.057
And you're very vocal about that.

22:17.157 --> 22:18.258
And that may be you.

22:19.039 --> 22:23.885
That tendency to reject God's authority is for some explicit.

22:23.905 --> 22:25.526
For others though, it's more implicit.

22:26.307 --> 22:36.018
Meaning, we maybe have embraced the gospel and we say, okay God, yeah, you can be Lord of these things, but not these things.

22:36.930 --> 22:41.034
You can begin to mess with my life here, but leave these alone.

22:42.676 --> 22:48.401
You can have these things or all begin to buy your grace, work on these things, but these things are untouchable.

22:48.902 --> 22:49.382
These are mine.

22:50.043 --> 22:56.890
And boy, if that's the case, we're suddenly rejecting the authority of God and pursuing our own authority.

22:57.390 --> 23:03.056
Second, is in some ways we still often want to live like the other nations.

23:04.037 --> 23:05.298
We don't want to be distinct.

23:06.018 --> 23:08.301
We want to be like them.

23:08.341 --> 23:09.663
I mean, they look happy.

23:09.983 --> 23:11.104
They look prosperous.

23:11.245 --> 23:12.747
They look successful.

23:13.007 --> 23:14.509
Why can't we be like them?

23:14.549 --> 23:19.435
And in some ways, we forget that we're actually not called to be friends with the world.

23:20.576 --> 23:23.700
In fact, John's going to tell us, do not love the world or anything in the world.

23:24.161 --> 23:26.964
If anyone loves the world, the love of the Father is not in Him.

23:27.705 --> 23:34.514
For all that's in the world, the lust of the flesh, the lust of the eyes and the boastful pride of life comes not from the Father, but from the world.

23:35.074 --> 23:42.186
Romans chapter 12 is going to say, therefore I urge you, brethren, by the mercies of God to offer yourself to God as a living sacrifice, holy and acceptable to God.

23:42.226 --> 23:44.109
This is your spiritual service of worship.

23:44.129 --> 23:49.478
And don't be conformed any longer to the patterns of this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind.

23:50.500 --> 24:00.978
Jesus will go as far as to say that if anyone wishes to come after me, he or she must deny themselves, take up their cross and follow me, for whoever wishes to save their life will lose it.

24:01.570 --> 24:11.241
But whoever loses their life for his sake and the gospels will actually find it and yet the irony is here we are wanting to live like the people of the world.

24:11.862 --> 24:16.487
But remember, we're called to be distinct and influence the world, not vice versa.

24:16.927 --> 24:18.910
But there's no neutral in the Christian life.

24:19.610 --> 24:24.296
We either are moving forward towards intimacy with God or we're drifting away.

24:24.576 --> 24:29.842
There's really no in between, which is why you see so many passages like Colossians 3

24:29.986 --> 24:33.953
that are going to invite us into that continual journey towards Christ.

24:33.973 --> 24:43.649
Where he says, therefore, if you have been raised up with Christ, keep seeking the things above where Christ is seated at the right hand of God.

24:44.310 --> 24:51.181
And set your mind on the things above, not on the things on earth, for you have died and your life is hidden with Christ in God.

24:51.963 --> 24:54.066
And so there is an invitation for us

24:54.210 --> 25:09.353
to not be like the other nations, to set our sights on Christ and to live the Christian life, which is a progressive journey every single day, every single moment of laying aside the old self and putting on the new self, which is being made into the likeness of Christ.

25:10.154 --> 25:22.072
And then third, I think it's interesting that we are so easily convinced even today that an earthly leader will solve our problems.

25:22.092 --> 25:23.634
So we start watching the news,

25:24.418 --> 25:31.429
We get caught in the death scroll, and we start reading things, and our blood pressure starts rising.

25:32.310 --> 25:35.896
And we start hearing about election years, and our blood pressure starts rising.

25:35.956 --> 25:43.888
And we start seeing political figures jockeying for position, beginning to get platformed, or being platformed, or posting stuff.

25:44.910 --> 25:46.112
And you're going, oh boy.

25:46.793 --> 25:49.557
And all of a sudden we start getting all amped up.

25:50.679 --> 25:52.562
And it's interesting, we assume

25:52.866 --> 26:00.700
that if the right politician or political party or earthly leader is in power, then we'll have peace.

26:02.162 --> 26:03.244
Then we'll have joy.

26:04.626 --> 26:05.708
Then we can be at rest.

26:06.770 --> 26:12.620
And if that's you, the problem is you are connecting your identity with a lesser thing.

26:13.863 --> 26:18.130
You are in some ways in meshing your hope

26:18.402 --> 26:23.068
with an earthly ruler that was never intended to be a functional savior.

26:23.789 --> 26:30.137
Now, it is interesting that we live in a culture where we have opportunities most Christians in the world don't have.

26:30.698 --> 26:32.239
We can go to a polling place.

26:33.061 --> 26:35.804
We can pull a lever for a candidate or a party.

26:36.285 --> 26:40.590
We get to participate in our republic, which is wonderful.

26:41.031 --> 26:41.731
What a gift.

26:42.232 --> 26:43.193
But here's the problem.

26:43.814 --> 26:46.898
If you're biting your fingernails, watching the election results,

26:47.138 --> 26:48.901
It's gotta be my person.

26:49.722 --> 26:52.866
And if it's not your person, you're like, oh, what is going on here?

26:53.728 --> 26:56.051
You have yoked yourself to a lesser thing.

26:56.972 --> 27:00.398
And you will always be disappointed because they cannot give you peace.

27:00.518 --> 27:01.599
Only he can give you peace.

27:01.619 --> 27:03.883
There is a king of kings and a Lord of lords.

27:03.983 --> 27:05.625
Now, we need to be reminded.

27:06.547 --> 27:13.357
Paul tells us in Romans chapter 13 that every person is to be in subjection to governing authorities.

27:14.258 --> 27:17.042
For there is no authority except from God

27:17.218 --> 27:21.223
and those which exist are established by God.

27:22.164 --> 27:25.268
Which means sometimes you pull the lever and your person wins.

27:26.329 --> 27:29.954
Sometimes you pull the lever, meaning you vote, and your person doesn't win.

27:31.356 --> 27:32.677
But you could still sleep good at night.

27:34.139 --> 27:38.625
Because all authority, whether it's the person you wanted or not, is appointed by God.

27:39.346 --> 27:43.330
Which means we have a king of kings and a lord of lords, and he doesn't live downtown.

27:44.672 --> 27:46.194
And he doesn't live in Sacramento.

27:46.850 --> 27:48.351
and he doesn't live in the White House.

27:48.952 --> 27:50.293
Thank you, Jesus.

27:51.555 --> 28:04.688
He is in glory, which means then we have an opportunity to be at peace, because regardless of what we see happening in our world by way of lesser leaders, we have an ultimate leader, a king of kings, who never changes.

28:05.468 --> 28:13.236
What that means then also is we do have a responsibility, yes, to be in subjection to governing authorities, but also to pray for those who are in authority.

28:13.897 --> 28:15.058
Paul's gonna tell Timothy,

28:15.714 --> 28:23.005
to pray for kings and all those who are in authority so that we might live a peaceful tranquil and quiet life.

28:23.927 --> 28:26.791
Does your blood pressure start rising as you see the things on the news?

28:26.852 --> 28:32.540
Well, it sounds like you and I need to pray for that person and say, God, this person has lost their mind.

28:34.363 --> 28:34.744
Sick them.

28:37.689 --> 28:38.650
And then I'm gonna rest.

28:39.251 --> 28:43.698
I can be a peace and live a tranquil and quiet life because I know God ultimately

28:44.002 --> 28:47.446
You hold their heart in your hand and you channel it like waters.

28:47.546 --> 28:48.207
They're yours.

28:48.747 --> 28:51.470
You do it every, whether they know it or not, they're yours.

28:51.830 --> 28:56.796
So Lord, would you just do something in their life so I can sleep at night and in that we find peace?

28:56.836 --> 29:13.714
And so we need to pray, which means we need to pray for them, whether you voted for them or not, which means we need to support them by praying for them, whether you voted for them or not in hopes that their hearts would be opened to the Word of God and to the movement of the gospel.

29:13.794 --> 29:19.822
that they might, by God's grace, lead in such a way that's in keeping with the Scriptures.

29:20.883 --> 29:25.570
Psalm 147 reminds us that he does not delight in the strength of horses.

29:26.291 --> 29:28.654
He does not take pleasure in the legs of men.

29:29.415 --> 29:33.701
The Lord favors those who fear him, those who wait for his loving kindness.

29:34.602 --> 29:43.794
And so if you find yourself anxious because of these earthly kings, can we just be reminded that it's the king of kings and Lord of lords that we need to serve?

29:44.066 --> 29:50.472
And so I just ask as we come to a close, if I held that mirror up, is there anything there in your life?

29:52.334 --> 29:58.019
Have you found yourself maybe rejecting the authority of God either explicitly or implicitly?

29:59.100 --> 30:03.865
Have you found yourself saying, I don't need the work of the gospel, I don't believe in God, I think it's a fairy tale?

30:04.906 --> 30:06.868
Would you be open to maybe reconsider that?

30:07.848 --> 30:13.714
Because there is a truth of a God who loves you so much, that he wants a relationship with you and he wants to invite you out of autonomy

30:14.082 --> 30:15.924
into the richness of relationship with Him.

30:15.964 --> 30:20.070
And for those who've embraced the gospel, is there anything in your life that you're still holding on to?

30:21.211 --> 30:23.654
I mean, if you're gut level honest, have you said, you know what, Lauren?

30:24.716 --> 30:26.177
I have been crucified with Christ.

30:26.638 --> 30:28.480
It's no longer I who lives, it's Christ.

30:28.581 --> 30:31.304
God, you have access to everything.

30:31.324 --> 30:32.806
Search me, O God, and know my heart.

30:33.527 --> 30:36.070
Are you willing to do that, or is there something you're hanging on to?

30:37.051 --> 30:39.154
And would you be willing to bring that something into the light?

30:39.970 --> 30:53.287
And I would say also, as we talk about the double move of rejecting authority and pursuing our own, have we found ourselves trying to pursue authority on our own and be like the other nations?

30:53.307 --> 31:01.558
Do we find ourselves wanting what they have and being influenced by them opposed to us influencing the nations?

31:01.578 --> 31:07.666
And maybe finally, have you found your peace in or tried to find it at least in an earthly king?

31:08.162 --> 31:11.345
And if so, might it be worth us saying, you know what, Lord, that's a good reminder.

31:11.365 --> 31:13.087
I need to raise my sights to see you.

31:13.788 --> 31:19.193
Because I don't know what your blood pressure is like, but I'll tell you, I don't know why I look at the news.

31:21.635 --> 31:25.779
Because we're dealing with fallen people who make terrible decisions.

31:26.500 --> 31:29.643
And we just need to be reminded that it's Jesus who is our King.

31:30.364 --> 31:36.530
And regardless of what's happening here, our hope is fixed and nothing less than Jesus in His righteousness.

31:36.770 --> 31:39.334
And so can we raise our sights to Him, amen?

31:39.354 --> 31:39.814
Let's pray.

31:40.275 --> 31:55.576
Well, Father, I'm grateful for Your Word and grateful for the invitation that we have to submit to the King of Kings, who by Your grace, You've provided a means by which we can be reconciled to You because of Jesus and what He has done for us.

31:55.676 --> 32:02.866
And so I pray that we would be just at peace under Your rule and Your reign.

32:03.394 --> 32:11.333
Even though the storms are blowing, and even though the waves may crash, proverbially speaking, in our political environment, Lord, could we find peace in you?

32:11.994 --> 32:16.325
Because you are Lord of all, and you hold all of it in your hand.

32:16.886 --> 32:19.392
And so, well, thank you for all of it in Jesus' name.

32:20.174 --> 32:20.274
Amen.

